In the context of carbon emissions, one of the least expensive forms of media to load onto your device is text.
As shown above, websites like Google, which are relatively simple because they primarily show static text, have much lower emissions than websites like Facebook, which load a lot of data-heavy media types to your device.

### Audio
[LargeAside]
[ParametricGraphic hed:"Emissions of Audio" style:`{padding: 0}`]
[MediaPicker type:"bar" mediaType:"audio" data:mediaPickerData width:"100%" headers:false/]
[br/]
[caption]Each bar represents the carbon emitted when listening to an audio clip for 60 seconds.[/caption]
[/ParametricGraphic]
